@startuml ddc_acquisition_activity
!include dark-theme.puml
title DDC acquisition lifecycle - read first, write only by mode

start

:Acquisition trigger;
note right
  Startup, topology event, startup sweep,
  or DDC recovery can all enter here.
end note

:Enumerate displays without VCP writes;
:Reconcile identity and park missing known-DDC rows as Failed;

if (Recent topology event?) then (yes)
  :Wait remaining post-detection settle window;
else (no)
endif

:Phase B probe each enumerated display;
:Read resolved brightness VCP\n(profile/user override) with retry\nand final handle refresh;

if (Read succeeds?) then (yes)
  if (Existing MonitorInfo?) then (yes)
    :Install fresh DDC entry/handle;
    if (Has explicit user/profile slider value?) then (yes)
      :Preserve manual slider baseline;
    else (no)
      :Sync slider baseline from current DDC read\nwithout claiming user intent;
    endif
    :Recover SliderState using current curve flags;
  else (no)
    :Create MonitorInfo from current DDC read;
    :Saved profile may later restore manual UI state;
  endif
  :Mark row acquired;
else (no)
  :Add or keep row as Failed;
  :No automatic brightness write;
  stop
endif

:Apply bounds and norm-curve metadata\nwithout replaying hardware;
:Record DDC-capable observation;
:Raise MonitorsAcquired(acquired rows);

if (Brightness curve enabled?) then (yes)
  :EnvironmentalCurveService evaluates;
  if (Offset mode?) then (yes)
    :Write per-monitor LastUserBrightness + offset;
  else (no)
    :Write absolute curve value to each curve-owned row;
  endif
elseif (Row disabled by user?) then (yes)
  :Write nothing;
elseif (Acquired row has explicit user/profile manual value?) then (yes)
  :Write that row's manual slider value to DDC\nscaled by the row's last known VCP max;
else (no)
  :Write nothing\n(current DDC read is already the UI baseline);
endif

:Raise MonitorsRefreshed;
:Recompute master slider from connected\nhardware-functional displays using MasterSliderMode;
note right
  Master recompute is UI state only.
  Adding a display must not replay writes
  to already-connected displays.
end note

stop
@enduml
